59.9	Donald_Barthelme	Donald Barthelme	Donald Barthelme (April 7, 1931 – July 23, 1989) was an American author known for his playful, postmodernist style of short fiction. Barthelme also worked as a newspaper reporter for the Houston Post, managing editor of Location magazine, director of the Contemporary Arts Museum in Houston (1961–1962), co-founder of Fiction (with Mark Mirsky and the assistance of Max and Marianne Frisch), and a professor at various universities. He also was one of the original founders of The University of Houston Creative Writing Program.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d2/Donald_Barthelme_%28author%29.jpg/220px-Donald_Barthelme_%28author%29.jpg
